    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 2.5",
    "body" : "<p>Some conventions list all the public methods first, and then all the private ones - that means it's easy to separate the API from the implementation, even when there's no interface involved, if you see what I mean.</p>\n\n<p>Another idea is to group related methods together - this makes it easier to spot seams where you could split your existing large class into several smaller, more targeted ones.</p>\n"
