      "body" : "what is the ordering convention when we have static variables, static blocks, static methods, constructors, instance variables and instance methods ?"
    }, {
      "owner" : {
        "account_id" : 238697,
        "reputation" : 2019,
        "user_id" : 507761,
        "user_type" : "registered",
        "accept_rate" : 100,
        "profile_image" : "https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/1a777be80e0c463a139e737821941952?s=256&d=identicon&r=PG",
        "display_name" : "Matthew Read",
        "link" : "https://stackoverflow.com/users/507761/matthew-read"
      },
      "edited" : false,
      "score" : 0,
      "creation_date" : 1742345935,
      "post_id" : 12427127,
      "comment_id" : 140235780,
      "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 4.0",
      "body" : "Static blocks only exist for nontrivial initialization of static variables, so the static block comes immediately after the static vars.  The rest is already clear from the answer.  I will add that I&#39;ve encountered multiple tools that extend the static&gt;instance, public&gt;package&gt;protected&gt;private ordering to methods."
    } ],
    "owner" : {
      "account_id" : 255148,
      "reputation" : 14316,
      "user_id" : 534994,
      "user_type" : "registered",
      "accept_rate" : 93,
      "profile_image" : "https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/c10bfa58600b422a1462669b898d3ad7?s=256&d=identicon&r=PG",
      "display_name" : "Michael",
